newsitem.title: SINGAPORE: Singapore rubber futures end flat, seen to drift.
newsitem.headline: Singapore rubber futures end flat, seen to drift.

text.p: Rubber futures closed virtually unchanged on Wednesday in thin, lacklustre trading with the market weighed down by a lack of buying orders from major consumers, dealers said.
"We're not really seeing any firm buying interest at all. There's nothing fantastic going on. It's just drifting along," a local rubber trader said.
Moderate buying yesterday, especially for RSS3 rubber, quickly fizzled out.
"It's a soft market looking for direction to give it fresh leads," another trader said.
At around 0945 GMT, December RSS3 was seen steady at 127.25 U.S. cents a kg.
December RSS1 was seen at 180.00-182.00 Singapore cents (US$1.27-$1.29) a kg from 181.00 cents.
December TSR20 was seen at 175.50 Singapore cents (US$1.24) a kg from the previous 175.75 cents.
